   "source": [
    "COVID-19 Global case analysis (2020-2021)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "3b6412d4-18f1-42f6-85a8-58dfa000a365",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Introduction:\n",
    ">>  COVID-19 emerged as a global health crisis in early 2020,affecting millions of people worldwide.\n",
    ">>  Understanding the progression of confirmed cases,recoveries and deaths across countries is crucial for analyzing the \n",
    "    impact of the pandemic and identifying patterns in its spread.\n",
    ">>  This project focuses on the data containing confirmed cases,recoveries and deaths from almost all countries between \n",
    "    \"22 January 2020\" and \"29 May 2021\"."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "09ba34ec-b027-4149-91f3-9a084f4f0801",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Objective:\n",
    " To perform Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) using Python to clean the data and uncover trends,visualize the progression \n",
    " of the pandemic and highlight differences across regions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "2c8eab82-3a44-451e-b077-c503a5d978b2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Tools used: Python, Pandas, Numpy, Matplotlib, Seaborn."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "482449d7-8279-49c3-b9de-d408e3d5d976",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Expected Outcome:  \n",
    " Clear insights into case growth,recovery rates and mortality trends supported by visualizations that make the data easy to interpret."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "6834a765-7046-4bd6-918d-0caf6e5d43ee",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Table of contents:\n",
    "    >> Importing the necessary libraries.\n",
    "    >> Importing the required datasets.\n",
    "    >> Checking for null values and replacing them with preferred values.\n",
    "    >> Defining date functions for further use.\n",
    "    >> Task 1: Line plot of confirmed cases,recoveries and deaths of COVID-19 pandemic in top 3 countries.\n",
    "    >> Task 2: Generate a lineplot for top 3 states from china with the highest confirmed cases.\n",
    "    >> Task 3: Peak Daily COVID‑19 Cases in Germany,Italy and France.\n",
    "    >> Task 4: Recovery rate(recovered cases/confirmed cases) comparision between Canada and Australia as of 31 December 2020.\n",
    "    >> Task 5: Provincial COVID‑19 Death Rate Distribution in Canada.\n",
    "    >> Task 6: COVID‑19 Deaths in the United States (Line Plot).\n",
    "    >> Task 7: Top 5 Countries by Total COVID‑19 Deaths.\n",
    "    >> Task 8: Top 5 Countries by Average Daily COVID‑19 Deaths.\n",
    "    >> Task 9: Monthly analysis of COVID‑19 cases,deaths and recoveries in the US, Italy, and Brazil.\n",
    "    >> Task 10: Top 5 Countries by COVID‑19 Death Rate (2020).\n",
    "    >> Task 11: For South Africa compare the total number of recoveries to total number of deaths.\n",
    "    >> Task 12: For USA,analyze the ratio of recovered cases to confirmed cases on a monthly basis from march 2020 to may 2021 and identify the month         with the highest recovery rate.\n",
    "    >> Task 13: Correlation Analysis of COVID‑19 Variables in US,Brazil and India.\n",
    "    >> Project closing statement.\n",
    "    >> Future work."
   ]
  },
