   "id": "9e189985-ef55-4edf-b20c-a19c8b0f8522",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Task 3: Peak Daily COVID‑19 Cases in Germany,Italy and France."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e26ee87b-9204-42b9-93c0-c5ca32f676b6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This analysis identifies the peak number of daily new COVID‑19 cases in Germany, Italy, and France, and highlights which country experienced the highest single‑day surge along with the date it occurred.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 157,
   "id": "fb70d12b-805f-4500-9b8e-17d568b1197e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# filtering the confirmed cases dataset for countries Germany , Italy and France.\n",
    "dff1=df_c[df_c[\"Country/Region\"].isin([\"Germany\",\"Italy\",\"France\"])]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 159,
   "id": "8d6086e4-0153-4373-8e7c-ce3883381ab2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Grouping by country so that all the provinces/states of that country are summed up using gropuby() function.\n",
    "dff11=dff1.groupby(\"Country/Region\").sum()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 161,
   "id": "e238dd02-f9e8-4f2c-afef-7c65e3184ef1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Dropping the province/state column because it has nothing to do with our further analysis.\n",
    "dff11=dff11.drop(columns=[\"Province/State\"])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 163,
   "id": "7298a19d-114b-44e5-bb88-18261d70e007",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "France-cases=117900.0 on 4-Nov.1\n",
      "Germany-cases=49044.0 on 12/30/2020\n",
      "Italy-cases=40902.0 on 11/13/2020\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# looping over the rows to get the peak dialy cases and the date for every country.\n",
    "for i,j in dff11.iterrows():\n",
    "    dialy_cases=j.astype(int).diff()\n",
    "    max_cases=dialy_cases.max()\n",
    "    max_date=dialy_cases[dialy_cases.values==max_cases].index[0]\n",
    "    print(f\"{i}-cases={max_cases} on {max_date}\")\n",
    "    "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5818c4c2-4cb5-4130-83ab-582adea53db0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Analysis outcome : France experienced the highest single‑day surge in daily new COVID‑19 cases, recording 1,17,900 infections on 11 April 2021.In comparison, Germany’s peak was 49,044 cases on 30 December 2020, and Italy’s peak was 40,902 cases on 13 November 2020."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 375,
   "id": "a68b23ec-76d1-47aa-82d4-c2aa4710d63b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#################################################################"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "de819d91-5ce1-44fb-bfad-7a9c3473d8fb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Task 4: Recovery rate(recovered cases/confirmed cases) comparision between Canada and Australia as of 31 December 2020."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "92dde57a-5675-4245-bf85-aa44fcd3de45",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    " This task calculates and compares the recovery rates (recovered cases/confirmed cases) between Canada and Australia as of December 31, 2020, to determine which country achieved a better recovery outcome."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 173,
   "id": "879498a2-f0f5-4d31-a544-3d68b4b347ab",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Filtering the confirmed cases and recoveries datasets for countries Canada and Australia.\n",
    "res_c1=df_c[df_c[\"Country/Region\"].isin([\"Canada\",\"Australia\"])]\n",
    "res_r1=df_r[df_r[\"Country/Region\"].isin([\"Canada\",\"Australia\"])]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 177,
   "id": "de4fad2b-2b13-4678-b897-13e0d4c96e85",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Considering only required columns using loc[] function\n",
    "res_c1=res_c1.loc[:,[\"Country/Region\",\"12/31/2020\"]]\n",
    "res_r1=res_r1.loc[:,[\"Country/Region\",\"12/31/2020\"]]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 178,
   "id": "1731e6f5-c267-42c2-a14d-c20f83d5f02f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "res_c11=res_c1.groupby(\"Country/Region\").sum()\n",
    "res_r11=res_r1.groupby(\"Country/Region\").sum()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 180,
   "id": "3142a563-a2e6-4bbf-8b9d-2397c86f5301",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# resetting the index\n",
    "res_r11=res_r11.reset_index()\n",
    "res_c11=res_c11.reset_index()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 182,
   "id": "1c71f61e-2961-4ee5-8d0f-19741b586d37",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Renaming the columns \n",
    "res_c11=res_c11.rename(columns={\"12/31/2020\":\"confirmed_cases\"})\n",
    "res_r11=res_r11.rename(columns={\"12/31/2020\":\"recovered_cases\"})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 184,
   "id": "9cb2eb77-c518-47fa-8c12-1c1299da9b59",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Merging the resultant datasets using pd.merge() function\n",
    "combined=pd.merge(res_c11,res_r11,on=\"Country/Region\")"
   ]
  },
  {
