   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In the United States,September 2020 recorded the highest COVID‑19 recovery rate, marking the peak month for patient recoveries during that year."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "id": "e6b7050a-62bf-446f-90e8-c4a9ca43a5b1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#######################################################"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a74d1b70-cab6-4eda-96ec-3b86e38150a1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Task 13: Correlation Analysis of COVID‑19 Variables in US,Brazil and India."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3780cca7-e807-4c0f-87e8-ca4cc81d8afb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "For this analysis,I have focused on the United States,Brazil and India because these countries reported the highest number of confirmed cases and deaths over time.Studying them provides meaningful insights into the relationship between cases,deaths and recoveries in regions most severely impacted by the pandemic."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 304,
   "id": "66dc911a-4d8e-4a80-b8d1-56fd945d6765",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#filtering the datsets for US,Brazil and India.considering:\n",
    "# c for confirmed cases\n",
    "# r for recoveries\n",
    "# d for deaths\n",
    "C=df_c[df_c[\"Country/Region\"].isin([\"US\",\"Brazil\",\"India\"])].iloc[:,1:].T.reset_index().rename(columns={\"index\":\"Date\",30:\"c_Brazil\",147:\"c_India\",251:\"c_US\"}).iloc[1:,:]\n",
    "D=df_d[df_d[\"Country/Region\"].isin([\"US\",\"Brazil\",\"India\"])].iloc[:,1:].T.reset_index().rename(columns={\"index\":\"Date\",30:\"d_Brazil\",147:\"d_India\",267:\"d_US\"}).iloc[1:,:]\n",
    "R=df_r[df_r[\"Country/Region\"].isin([\"US\",\"Brazil\",\"India\"])].iloc[:,1:].T.reset_index().rename(columns={\"index\":\"Date\",30:\"r_Brazil\",132:\"r_India\",236:\"r_US\"}).iloc[1:,:]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 308,
   "id": "f37ab14c-14b1-462a-9298-8faf26588c4f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# merging the resultant df's\n",
    "\n",
    "merged=pd.merge(C,D,on=\"Date\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 309,
   "id": "d38f14e8-7991-4583-bff8-ed183513fb30",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "merged1=pd.merge(merged,R,on=\"Date\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 316,
   "id": "86b25dab-d6cf-4a17-a029-0bfd1f5b5f56",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "India:Confirmed vs Deaths:  0.99\n",
      "India:Confirmed vs Recoveries:  1.0\n",
      "India:Deaths vs Recoveries:  0.99\n",
      "US:Confirmed vs Deaths:  0.99\n",
      "US:Confirmed vs Recoveries:  -0.22\n",
      "US:Deaths vs Recoveries:  -0.14\n",
      "Brazil:Confirmed vs Deaths:  0.99\n",
      "Brazil:Confirmed vs Recoveries:  1.0\n",
      "Brazil:Deaths vs Recoveries:  0.99\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# finding the correlation among US, India, Brazil for confirmed cases, deaths, recoveries.\n",
    "\n",
    "# India: confirmed vs deaths\n",
    "corr_india_cd=round(merged1[\"c_India\"].corr(merged1[\"d_India\"]).item(),2)\n",
    "print(\"India:Confirmed vs Deaths: \",corr_india_cd)\n",
    "\n",
    "# India: confirmed vs recoveries\n",
    "corr_india_cr=round(merged1[\"c_India\"].corr(merged1[\"r_India\"]).item(),2)\n",
    "print(\"India:Confirmed vs Recoveries: \",corr_india_cr)\n",
    "\n",
    "# India: deaths vs recoveries\n",
    "corr_india_dr=round(merged1[\"d_India\"].corr(merged1[\"r_India\"]).item(),2)\n",
    "print(\"India:Deaths vs Recoveries: \",corr_india_dr)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# US: confirmed vs deaths\n",
    "corr_us_cd=round(merged1[\"c_US\"].corr(merged1[\"d_US\"]).item(),2)\n",
    "print(\"US:Confirmed vs Deaths: \",corr_us_cd)\n",
    "\n",
    "# US: confirmed vs recoveries\n",
    "corr_us_cr=round(merged1[\"c_US\"].corr(merged1[\"r_US\"]).item(),2)\n",
    "print(\"US:Confirmed vs Recoveries: \",corr_us_cr)\n",
    "\n",
    "# US: deaths vs recoveries\n",
    "corr_us_dr=round(merged1[\"d_US\"].corr(merged1[\"r_US\"]).item(),2)\n",
    "print(\"US:Deaths vs Recoveries: \",corr_us_dr)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Brazil: confirmed vs deaths\n",
    "corr_brazil_cd=round(merged1[\"c_Brazil\"].corr(merged1[\"d_Brazil\"]).item(),2)\n",
    "print(\"Brazil:Confirmed vs Deaths: \",corr_brazil_cd)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Brazil: confirmed vs recoveries\n",
    "corr_brazil_cr=round(merged1[\"c_Brazil\"].corr(merged1[\"r_Brazil\"]).item(),2)\n",
    "print(\"Brazil:Confirmed vs Recoveries: \",corr_brazil_cr)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Brazil: deaths vs recoveries\n",
    "corr_brazil_dr=round(merged1[\"d_Brazil\"].corr(merged1[\"r_Brazil\"]).item(),2)\n",
    "print(\"Brazil:Deaths vs Recoveries: \",corr_brazil_dr)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "415cdfa0-55ad-4517-8d2e-c906903ffcc4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Interpretation:\n",
    "The correlation analysis reveals that India and Brazil show extremely strong positive correlations across confirmed cases,deaths and recoveries,indicating that these variables moved almost perfectly in sync over time.In contrast,the \"United States\" shows a strong correlation between confirmed cases and deaths,but a negative correlation with recoveries,suggesting inconsistencies in recovery reporting or differences in how recoveries were tracked compared to cases and deaths.Overall,this highlights that while the pandemic trends were tightly linked in India and Brazil,the US data reflects a more complex relationship between infections,fatalities and recoveries."
   ]
  },
